Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve the @bell pepper{2} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @lime{1}.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}. Pop half into a #bowl{} and roughly mash with the back of a #fork{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the pepper and @sliced mushrooms{180%g}. Stir-fry until just soft, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone.

Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out onto a #board{}.

Cut into 1cm chunks.

Once the veg has softened, add the @chipotle paste{1%tsp}, @vegetable stock paste{1%tsp}, garlic, black beans (whole and crushed) and @water{50%ml} to the pan.

Cook, stirring, until the liquid has reduced and the mixture has thickened slightly, ~{1-2%minutes}.

When the fajita filling is ready, squeeze in some lime juice and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix well, then remove the heat.

Meanwhile, pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} onto a #baking tray{} and into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

In another small bowl, mix together the @soured cream{75%g} and lime zest.

Cut any remaining lime into wedges.

When everything's ready, lay your tortillas onto your plates (3 per person).

Spread over a spoonful of the zesty soured cream, then top with the fajita filling and avocado - as much as you'd like.

Serve any remaining lime wedges alongside for squeezing over.

Enjoy!